      "number": 14,
      "id": "PR_kwDONMXNnM6EcfB0",
      "title": "fix(linux): use IP*_PMTUDISC_PROBE",
      "url": "https://github.com/marten-seemann/draft-seemann-tsvwg-udp-fragmentation/pull/14",
      "state": "MERGED",
      "author": "mxinden",
      "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "1. Use `IP*_PMTUDISC_PROBE` instead of `IP*_PMTUDISC_DO`, in order to disable Linux's own PMTUD and to send packets larger than the observed Path MTU.\r\n2. Use `IP*_DONTFRAG` to receive errors when sending packets larger than the interface MTU.\r\n---\r\nFixes #13 \r\n\r\n@marten-seemann and @ralith this is my understanding of the socket options. Thoughts?",
      "createdAt": "2024-12-08T15:00:37Z",
      "updatedAt": "2025-02-26T18:53:35Z",
      "baseRepository": "marten-seemann/draft-seemann-tsvwg-udp-fragmentation",
