          "authorAssociation": "NONE",
          "state": "COMMENTED",
          "body": "",
          "createdAt": "2024-12-08T20:55:01Z",
          "updatedAt": "2024-12-08T20:55:01Z",
          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 20,
              "body": "Also, how certain are you that `mtu` is necessarily the *interface* mtu and not some guess of the path MTU?",
              "createdAt": "2024-12-08T20:55:01Z",
              "updatedAt": "2024-12-08T20:55:01Z"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "PRR_kwDONMXNnM6URsom",
          "commit": {
            "abbreviatedOid": "d4c1bf0"
          },
          "author": "marten-seemann",
          "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
          "state": "COMMENTED",
          "body": "Can you also update the code in `code/main.c`?\r\n\r\nMaybe we could use that script to figure out what IPV6_DONTFRAG does as well?",
          "createdAt": "2024-12-09T03:55:13Z",
          "updatedAt": "2024-12-09T03:58:38Z",
          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 15,
              "body": "Isn't this backwards? The kernel doesn't even try to observe the Path MTU if IP_PMTUDISC_PROBE is set, it only does that for IP_PMTUDISC_DO.",
              "createdAt": "2024-12-09T03:55:13Z",
              "updatedAt": "2024-12-09T03:58:38Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 20,
              "body": "I'm still confused about IPV6_DONTFRAG, but with IP_PMTUDISC_DO the kernel processes ICMP packets, and refuses to send packets larger than the MTU advertised in that packet. \r\n\r\nAnd since ICMP packets are not end-to-end authenticated, this was what caused https://github.com/quic-go/quic-go/security/advisories/GHSA-px8v-pp82-rcvr.",
              "createdAt": "2024-12-09T03:57:42Z",
              "updatedAt": "2024-12-09T03:58:38Z"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "PRR_kwDONMXNnM6VABq_",
          "commit": {
            "abbreviatedOid": "d4c1bf0"
          },
          "author": "mxinden",
          "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
          "state": "COMMENTED",
          "body": "",
          "createdAt": "2024-12-12T14:26:25Z",
          "updatedAt": "2024-12-12T14:26:25Z",
          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 20,
              "body": "> Also, how certain are you that `mtu` is necessarily the _interface_ mtu and not some guess of the path MTU?\r\n\r\nAccording to https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man7/ip.7.html:\r\n\r\n```\r\n              Path MTU discovery value   Meaning\r\n              IP_PMTUDISC_WANT           Use per-route settings.\r\n              IP_PMTUDISC_DONT           Never do Path MTU Discovery.\r\n              IP_PMTUDISC_DO             Always do Path MTU Discovery.\r\n              IP_PMTUDISC_PROBE          Set DF but ignore Path MTU.\r\n```\r\n\r\nThus I assume with `IP_PMTUDISC_PROBE` the path MTU is always ignored. Does that make sense @Ralith?",
              "createdAt": "2024-12-12T14:26:25Z",
              "updatedAt": "2024-12-12T14:26:25Z"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "PRR_kwDONMXNnM6VCrEi",
