          "updatedAt": "2024-12-16T07:19:26Z",
          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 13,
              "body": "\"should be set independently\" doesn't make a lot of sense to me. I think \"can\" as better, as we want to point out that on Linux, one does not influence the other (this is different on macOS, for example).",
              "createdAt": "2024-12-16T07:19:26Z",
              "updatedAt": "2024-12-16T07:19:26Z"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "PRR_kwDONMXNnM6VVF_2",
          "commit": {
            "abbreviatedOid": "f69feb8"
          },
          "author": "marten-seemann",
          "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
          "state": "COMMENTED",
          "body": "",
          "createdAt": "2024-12-16T07:21:18Z",
          "updatedAt": "2024-12-16T07:25:44Z",
          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 17,
              "body": "Doesn't IPV6_PMTUDISC_PROBE already do that?",
              "createdAt": "2024-12-16T07:21:18Z",
              "updatedAt": "2024-12-16T07:25:44Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 6,
              "body": "I don't think Linux runs PMTUD on its own, in the sense that it sends probe packets on its own. Even with IP_PMTUDISC_DO, it would still be the application's responsibility to send a probe packet, the Linux kernel would just update its MTU tracking for this 4-tuple when it receives an ICMP packet.\r\n\r\nTherefore, I'd prefer to say something like this:\r\n1. IP_PMTUDISC_DO turns on the DF bit, and enables the processing of ICMP packets by the kernel\r\n2. IP_PMTUDISC_PROBE turns on the DF bit, and disables the processing of ICMP packets by the kernel\r\n\r\nWe can then point out that IP_PMTUDISC_DO is problematic from a security standpoint (and maybe cite the draft in dnsops?).",
              "createdAt": "2024-12-16T07:25:41Z",
              "updatedAt": "2024-12-16T07:25:44Z"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "PRR_kwDONMXNnM6VXZnv",
          "commit": {
